result.execSummary:
The defendant Valangel M Stinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Valangel M Stinson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Valangel M Stinson was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property >$10,000, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Valangel M Stinson was found guilty of Operate Vehicle w/o Consent-Passenger, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(4m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Valangel M Stinson in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations, and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 1 and COUNT 2 DISMISSED.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to COUNTS 4 and 6 pursuant to the Amended Information.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon she may no longer use or possess any firearms; also she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been restored.  Court further advised that if she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 4:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 1/2 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 1/2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS.   Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions for probation and extended supervision:
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program. 
-Restitution set at $1,746.00 payable to Jan H. joint/several with co-actor Alonte Wren 15CF1730
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments to be collected during term probation.  If defendant is revoked, all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds. Nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation. If defendant is revoked, all related surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with agent
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation and extended supervision
-Pay all supervision fees 
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-No contact with Jan H. 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Court allows expungement if defendant successfully completed terms and conditions of probation and has made at least $700.00 towards restitution

AS TO COUNT 6:
Court ordered defendant serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent with COUNT 4. 
-Court WAIVES Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments as defendant has a large amount of restitution to be paid back and payment of costs would be burdensome on the defendant.
-Defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay related surcharges during term of probaiton on COUNT 4

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon she may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been restored.

Filed, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence
Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief

Original Second Amended Information received and filed; COUNT 4:  Attempt Theft from Person - PTAC, As a Party to a Crime, pursuant to Wisc. Stats. 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(e), a Class G Felony and COUNT 6:  Operating Vehicle Without Owner's Consent (Knowing Passenger), pursuant to Wisc. Stats. 943.23, a Class A Misdemeanor.
